This demo demonstrates a more complex IceFIX deployment using
IceGrid.

The demo configures IceFIX bridges for two trading partners TP1 and
TP2.

TP1 is configured to use a QuickFIX configuration contained in
config.fix-tp1. This configuration creates a file system store,
contained in the directory store-tp1. The associated Freeze databases
are contained in db-tp1.

TP2 is likewise configured, except the file suffixes are tp2.

To run the demo, first start the IceGrid service.

$ icegridnode --Ice.Config=config.grid

In a separate window:

$ icegridadmin --Ice.Config=config.grid -e \
    "application add 'application.xml'"

Messages will be displayed in the IceGrid service window.

Next start an QuickFIX sample ordermatch server for each trading
partner.

$ ordermatch config.tp1

In a separate window, start the second ordermatch server.

$ ordermatch config.tp2

Now activate the bridges.

$ icefixadmin --Ice.Config=config.admin -e activate TP1
$ icefixadmin --Ice.Config=config.admin -e activate TP2

Now, run the client.

$ client --Ice.Config=config.client
